es.deusto.ingenieria.aike.formulation

Class Problem

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.deusto.ingenieria.aike.formulation.Problem

  • public abstract class Problem
extends java.lang.Object
    // * Class defining a problem's formulation for it to be solved by a search method. The problem is defined by:
  • List of initial states.
  • List of final states.
  • List of operators.

      • isFinalState

        public boolean isFinalState(State state)
        Checks whether a given state is one of the problem's final states by looking for it inside the problem's final states list (using method contains). If final states of the problem are unknown, this method must be redefined.
        Parameters:
        state - State containing the problem state to be checked.
        Returns:
        boolean
      • true - if state is found in the list of final states
      • false - if state is not found in the list of final states.
